# ğŸ§  Bad Habit Tracker API â€” Week 2

This week builds on the Week 1 foundation by adding a **habit logging system** and **replacement plans** that help users monitor, manage, and replace bad habits with positive ones.

---

## ğŸ¯ Week 2 Goals

- âœ… Allow users to **log habit occurrences** (daily, weekly, monthly)
- âœ… Compute and summarize **habit frequency** over time
- âœ… Add and manage **replacement plans** for each habit
- âœ… Display logs and replacement activities via API endpoints

---

## ğŸ§© Features Added This Week

### ğŸ”¹ Habit Logging
Users can record when they perform or avoid a habit.
- Track daily, weekly, and monthly progress.
- Prevent duplicate logs per day.
- Calculate completion streaks or frequencies.

### ğŸ”¹ Replacement Plans
Users can define alternative activities to replace bad habits.
- Each plan belongs to a specific habit.
- Encourages substitution behavior to reduce bad habit recurrence.

---

## âš™ï¸ Setup Instructions

If you already completed Week 1, your environment is ready.  
Otherwise, follow the quick setup below ğŸ‘‡

### 1ï¸âƒ£ Activate your virtual environment
```bash
venv\Scripts\activate     # Windows
# or
source venv/bin/activate  # macOS/Linux
````

### 2ï¸âƒ£ Install dependencies

```bash
pip install django djangorestframework djangorestframework-simplejwt
